title: 2012 Timewave zero & Fractal Time Software
description:
"2012 Timewave zero & Fractal Time Software developed by Peter Meyer & Terrence Mckenna"

This is a package of software programs developed by Peter Meyer & Terrence Mckenna, to chart time as a graph. Create your own charts and monitor the coming changes leading to Dec 21,2012 as the ZERO date on the chart, or alternatively see where history has been in the past on the chart.

File Descriptions below;

Timewave Zero v4.30 for DOS is a precision instrument for exploring the theory of time as a fractal wave derived from the King Wen sequence of I Ching Hexagrams. Based on extraterrestrial communications to Terence McKenna. Software developed by Peter Meyer. Published by Dolphin Software.
Fractal Time v1.23 by Peter Meyer.
wen_grph.zip takes a representation of a hexagram sequence, constructs the intermediate graphs then calculates the 384 data points. Author: Peter Meyer
tw.zip calculates the value of the timewave at a point. Author: Peter Meyer

Total size: 381.73 kilobyte
